Partitioning is more a generic term for dividing data across tables or databases. 
e.g. Dynamodb - partition key, e.g. emailId

Sharding is one specific type of partitioning, namely "horizontal partitioning", on multiple servers.
If one of servers is down, we didn't lose all the data.


Choosing the Right DynamoDB Partition Key
https://aws.amazon.com/blogs/database/choosing-the-right-dynamodb-partition-key/